{
  "name": "two-related-changes-to-the-20260408-0320",
  "idea": "Two related changes to the tool sidebar / default landing tool. (1) Make the default landing tool user-configurable. Currently visiting the app lands the user on the 'travel between images' tool (video-travel). Add a 'home' button on each tool entry in the tool sidebar. Clicking the home button on a tool sets it as the default \u2014 that's the tool the user lands on when they visit the app. The currently-set default should be visually highlighted in the sidebar (the home icon highlights for that item). (2) Promote the video-editor tool to be a 'main tool' \u2014 i.e., listed alongside the other main tools in the sidebar (not in a secondary section), and eligible to be set as the default via the same home-button mechanism from change #1. Investigate the codebase to understand: where the tool sidebar is rendered, how tools are listed/grouped, where the current default landing route is set, whether video-editor is currently in a separate category, and where user preferences are stored (settings table, localStorage, etc.). Then plan the minimal set of changes to implement both. Reuse existing settings/preferences patterns rather than inventing new ones.",
